WEBVTT

00:01.583 --> 00:03.043
You are being watched.

00:04.107 --> 00:06.231
The government has
a secret system.

00:06.412 --> 00:10.069
A machine that spies on you
every hour of every day.

00:10.670 --> 00:12.965
I know because I built it.

00:13.316 --> 00:15.582
I designed the machine to
detect acts of terror,

00:15.675 --> 00:17.190
but it sees everything.

00:17.329 --> 00:20.220
Violet crimes involving
ordinary people.

00:20.222 --> 00:21.638
People like you.

00:21.640 --> 00:25.442
Crimes the government
considered irrelevant.

00:25.444 --> 00:28.996
They wouldn't act,
so I decided I would.

00:28.998 --> 00:30.797
But I needed a partner.

00:30.799 --> 00:33.367
Someone with the skills
to intervene.

00:33.369 --> 00:37.487
Hunted by the authorities,
we work in secret.

00:37.489 --> 00:39.373
You'll never find us.

00:39.375 --> 00:42.898
But victim or perpetrator,
if your number's up,

00:43.081 --> 00:44.602
we'll find you.

00:46.239 --> 00:49.555
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

00:55.840 --> 00:57.674
Hey, it's me.

00:57.676 --> 01:00.444
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I got tied up here at work.

01:00.446 --> 01:01.445
[Elevator bell dings]

01:01.447 --> 01:03.147
I was thinking we could
grab a bite, okay?

01:03.149 --> 01:04.281
Usual place.

01:04.283 --> 01:08.518
Okay, see you in 30.
Yeah, bye.

01:08.520 --> 01:11.905
Hold it.

01:11.907 --> 01:14.374
Almost missed it.

01:18.213 --> 01:19.863
Those for your wife?

01:19.865 --> 01:23.383
Uh, yes.

01:23.385 --> 01:26.203
I thought your wife
liked roses.

01:26.205 --> 01:27.888
Excuse me.

01:27.890 --> 01:29.139
Do I know you?

01:29.141 --> 01:30.424
No.

01:30.426 --> 01:32.559
But I know you, Bill.

01:32.561 --> 01:34.311
Little relationship advice,

01:34.313 --> 01:35.879
if you're gonna
step out on your wife,

01:35.881 --> 01:38.315
you need to think it through.

01:38.317 --> 01:40.601
Do you work here?

01:40.603 --> 01:42.019
Because if you do,
you're fired.

01:42.021 --> 01:44.772
I'm more like
an independent contractor.

01:44.774 --> 01:47.557
Now, you don't seem
like a bad guy, Bill.

01:47.559 --> 01:50.494
You and your wife
are having some problems.

01:50.496 --> 01:51.995
It happens.

01:51.997 --> 01:55.165
Well, some women
would just leave you.

01:55.167 --> 01:58.752
But some women, they might
just hire a couple of guys

01:58.754 --> 02:00.337
to come to your office,

02:00.339 --> 02:03.390
dismantle your
surveillance cameras

02:03.392 --> 02:05.909
to make it look like
a robbery gone wrong.

02:09.764 --> 02:12.983
[Gun firing]

02:13.818 --> 02:15.435
[Elevator dinging]

02:19.224 --> 02:22.142
I would call the police
and a good divorce lawyer.

02:22.144 --> 02:25.612
[Men groaning]

02:31.653 --> 02:36.323
[Telephone rings]

02:36.325 --> 02:38.141
I've got a job for you.

02:38.143 --> 02:40.978
High priority.
Triple your usual fee.

02:40.980 --> 02:43.797
What's the name?

02:48.636 --> 02:52.039
[Horn honks, cell phone rings]

02:52.041 --> 02:53.173
Yeah.

02:53.175 --> 02:56.109
Good morning, Finch.

02:56.111 --> 02:58.011
No problems last night.

02:58.013 --> 03:00.597
Two hit men were waiting
to kill a guy,

03:00.599 --> 03:01.849
just like you said they'd be.

03:01.851 --> 03:04.084
- I took care of it.
- Good.

03:04.086 --> 03:06.303
You should get some rest.

03:06.305 --> 03:08.105
Thought I'd do
a little research.

03:08.107 --> 03:11.058
I'll be interested
to hear what you discover.

03:11.060 --> 03:13.193
We need to meet later.

03:13.195 --> 03:14.878
Your machine kick out
another number?

03:14.880 --> 03:17.948
Somebody else is gonna
be involved in a crime?

03:17.950 --> 03:20.934
This one is somewhat unusual.

03:20.936 --> 03:23.086
I'll let you know where to go.

03:23.088 --> 03:27.708
And, Mr. Reese,
we'll meet on my schedule.

03:27.710 --> 03:30.878
Not yours.

03:31.829 --> 03:33.413
Detective Carter.

03:33.415 --> 03:34.715
Aren't you homicide?

03:34.717 --> 03:36.183
I don't have any
cold ones for you.

03:36.185 --> 03:38.452
Just a couple of guys ain't
ever gonna play golf again.

03:38.454 --> 03:40.821
Yeah, it's part of
an ongoing investigation.

03:40.823 --> 03:42.189
What do we know
about the shooter?

03:42.191 --> 03:43.774
This rich guy
was on his way home,

03:43.776 --> 03:45.392
said a couple of guys
tried to kill him,

03:45.394 --> 03:46.860
and this, uh, other gentleman

03:46.862 --> 03:49.813
quote "intervened," unquote.

03:49.815 --> 03:53.617
Let me guess.
Some guy in a suit.

03:58.373 --> 04:00.457
How did your research go?

04:00.459 --> 04:02.659
Inconclusive.

04:02.661 --> 04:04.795
The number we've received

04:04.797 --> 04:07.214
is for a girl named
Theresa Whitaker.

04:07.216 --> 04:09.750
15 years old.

04:09.752 --> 04:11.585
Some disciplinary trouble,

04:11.587 --> 04:15.372
but basically a good kid.

04:15.374 --> 04:18.708
Well, the machine
did spit out her number,

04:18.709 --> 04:21.211
so she must be
caught up in something.

04:21.213 --> 04:23.814
Where can I find her?

04:26.184 --> 04:29.319
As I told you,
Mr. Reese,

04:29.321 --> 04:33.190
this situation
is somewhat unique.

04:33.192 --> 04:38.946
You see, Theresa Whitaker
should be right here.

04:41.899 --> 04:45.285
She was murdered, along with
the rest of her family.

04:45.287 --> 04:49.756
Two years ago.

04:49.758 --> 04:51.842
So we're looking for a ghost?

04:53.000 --> 04:59.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:36.951 --> 05:37.951
[Treadmill beeps]

05:37.953 --> 05:39.903
I thought you might
still be here.

05:39.905 --> 05:42.105
I come bearing gifts.
Whisky.

05:42.107 --> 05:43.073
Ah ha.

05:43.075 --> 05:44.491
And we won another award.

05:44.493 --> 05:47.277
[Laughs]

05:47.279 --> 05:48.611
Look, I know our deal.

05:48.613 --> 05:51.248
I schmooze the board,
I cash out the checks,

05:51.250 --> 05:54.501
I pick up the awards.
You do most of the work.

05:54.503 --> 05:58.138
But, honestly, this is getting
exhausting for me.

05:58.140 --> 06:00.724
I'm perfectly happy
with the division of labor.

06:00.726 --> 06:02.843
Always have been.

06:02.845 --> 06:04.461
What's this one for?

06:04.463 --> 06:07.681
This is for services
to humanity.

06:07.683 --> 06:09.683
I didn't tell them
that we laid off half the staff

06:09.685 --> 06:12.135
in order to build
this orwellian nightmare.

06:12.137 --> 06:13.737
Said you wanted
to make a difference,

06:13.739 --> 06:16.189
give something back.
This orwellian nightmare.

06:19.444 --> 06:21.194
Is this
is the government feeds?

06:21.196 --> 06:23.330
Direct from NSA at Fort Meade.

06:23.332 --> 06:26.649
That's every email,
every phone call,

06:26.651 --> 06:28.985
surveillance cameras...

06:28.987 --> 06:30.037
In the country?

06:30.039 --> 06:32.655
No, that's just New York.

06:32.657 --> 06:34.007
I'm starting
with the basics here.

06:34.009 --> 06:35.459
I'm trying to teach it
to track people

06:35.461 --> 06:36.793
using cell phone location data,

06:36.795 --> 06:38.161
facial recognition.

06:38.163 --> 06:40.497
I'm almost ready to move on
to the next problem.

06:40.499 --> 06:41.682
What's the next problem?

06:41.684 --> 06:43.934
Sorting them all out.

06:43.936 --> 06:46.219
Terrorists don't exactly stand
out on street corners, you know?

06:46.221 --> 06:48.772
You have to teach the machine
to sift through the emails,

06:48.774 --> 06:51.674
wire-tapped phones,
bank transactions,

06:51.676 --> 06:53.944
looking for people
that are hiding something,

06:53.946 --> 06:56.079
living double lives.

06:56.081 --> 06:57.981
People like you,
in other words.

06:57.983 --> 07:00.701
[Laughs]

07:00.703 --> 07:02.018
How long will this take?

07:02.020 --> 07:05.122
Four, five more years.

07:11.412 --> 07:13.547
So this is...

07:13.549 --> 07:16.049
Everyone.

07:16.051 --> 07:18.969
[Dramatic music]

07:18.971 --> 07:22.289
♪ ♪

07:32.500 --> 07:34.818
Nice spot.

07:39.056 --> 07:42.075
This is the last place
Theresa Whitaker was seen alive.

07:42.077 --> 07:43.777
Two years ago, her father Grant

07:43.779 --> 07:46.279
takes the family
for a weekend sail.

07:46.281 --> 07:48.665
No one comes home.

07:48.667 --> 07:50.333
Grant.

07:50.335 --> 07:52.735
He was a real estate developer.

07:52.737 --> 07:54.004
Market crashed.

07:54.006 --> 07:56.923
He was upside down
on 14 properties.

07:56.925 --> 07:59.042
According to the police,

07:59.044 --> 08:00.260
he shot his wife and kids,

08:00.262 --> 08:02.429
then turned the gun on himself.

08:02.431 --> 08:05.432
Says here they found
the bodies.

08:05.434 --> 08:08.301
Just the parents
and the 18-year-old son.

08:08.303 --> 08:11.304
Theresa's body
was never recovered.

08:11.306 --> 08:13.807
Uh, "presumed dead"?

08:13.809 --> 08:15.776
That's a reasonable assumption.

08:15.778 --> 08:19.146
The police only see
what they choose to look for.

08:19.148 --> 08:22.783
The machine sees
almost everything.

08:22.785 --> 08:24.518
If the girl's number
has come up,

08:24.520 --> 08:26.620
she must be alive.

08:26.622 --> 08:28.872
Then why hasn't she
shown up by now?

08:28.874 --> 08:31.107
With the police or a relative?

08:31.109 --> 08:33.159
I don't know.

08:33.162 --> 08:36.046
But if the machine is right
and she's still alive,

08:36.048 --> 08:38.414
she won't be for long.

08:39.616 --> 08:41.668
Better find her.

08:41.669 --> 08:44.304
I'll need a police report
on this.

08:44.306 --> 08:47.674
I'll have to talk to my friend
in the department.

08:59.153 --> 09:00.854
Hello, Lionel.

09:00.856 --> 09:02.989
You. Again.

09:02.991 --> 09:04.474
How the hell'd you get in here?

09:04.476 --> 09:06.827
Took it off your friend stills.

09:06.829 --> 09:08.445
The one I shot with your gun

09:08.447 --> 09:11.331
before you buried him
out in Oyster Bay.

09:11.333 --> 09:12.982
I need you to pull
a file for me.

09:12.984 --> 09:15.502
Yeah. Right after
you pull my IAD file.

09:15.504 --> 09:17.671
'Cause they got me
one step from fighting off

09:17.673 --> 09:20.156
a whole cellblock of degenerates
that I sent upstate.

09:20.158 --> 09:21.842
They think I'm dirty.

09:21.844 --> 09:24.344
That's because
you are dirty, Lionel.

09:24.346 --> 09:28.298
Look, your predicament
is not my doing or my concern.

09:28.300 --> 09:30.217
Name's Theresa Whitaker.

09:30.219 --> 09:35.004
Two-year-old murder-suicide
out in Bowery Bay.

09:35.006 --> 09:37.190
Get me the file.

09:44.065 --> 09:47.484
I just can't believe
that it came to this.

09:47.486 --> 09:50.186
We knew they were having,
uh, financial issues,

09:50.188 --> 09:52.021
but I never--
I never thought

09:52.023 --> 09:53.690
that he would do
anything like this.

09:53.692 --> 09:55.458
That's because he didn't.

09:55.460 --> 09:58.712
Wish that he would have...
Come to me.

09:58.714 --> 10:01.898
Wish he would have reached out.

10:01.900 --> 10:04.200
This was a professional hit.

10:04.202 --> 10:07.504
Muzzle impressions
were made after the fact,

10:07.506 --> 10:09.789
made it look point blank,

10:09.791 --> 10:10.924
like the father did it.

10:10.926 --> 10:12.425
Cops missed it.

10:12.427 --> 10:13.710
And you know that how?

10:13.712 --> 10:16.663
That's how I
would have done it.

10:19.350 --> 10:22.402
So why didn't the shooter
kill Theresa?

10:22.404 --> 10:24.020
That part I can't explain,

10:24.022 --> 10:26.106
or why she hasn't
shown up anywhere else.

10:26.108 --> 10:27.524
I've tracked down
a recent address

10:27.526 --> 10:29.576
for the aunt and uncle
in Brooklyn Heights.

10:29.578 --> 10:32.579
They might know what kind of
trouble Whitaker was in.

10:32.581 --> 10:33.947
I got a lead on another kid

10:33.949 --> 10:36.449
who might know her whereabouts.

10:36.451 --> 10:38.501
Sealed juvie record on Theresa.

10:38.503 --> 10:40.954
Seems she was picked up
with an older boy for vandalism,

10:40.956 --> 10:42.289
Deacon Page.

10:42.291 --> 10:45.241
Since, he's been popped
multiple times for shoplifting,

10:45.243 --> 10:46.543
carrying a concealed weapon.

10:46.545 --> 10:48.628
So if Theresa
didn't go to family,

10:48.630 --> 10:51.581
maybe she went to friends.

10:51.583 --> 10:53.850
But we don't know how much
time Theresa has left.

10:53.852 --> 10:56.419
Might need a little help,
Finch.

11:03.694 --> 11:06.229
[Doorbell rings]

11:06.231 --> 11:09.733
Hello. Arthur Bellinger,
Liberty State Mutual.

11:09.735 --> 11:11.034
Elizabeth Whitaker?

11:11.036 --> 11:12.268
Yes?

11:12.270 --> 11:15.989
We wrote the term life
policies for Grant Whitaker.

11:15.991 --> 11:19.709
You and your husband Derek
are listed as next of kin?

11:19.711 --> 11:20.660
Ex-husband.

11:20.662 --> 11:22.996
The divorce
went through last year.

11:22.998 --> 11:25.081
- Come in.
- Thank you.

11:25.083 --> 11:28.668
In cases like this involving
prolonged legal investigation,

11:28.670 --> 11:31.004
it can take some time
to settle out.

11:31.006 --> 11:32.472
I'm surprised
my brother-in-law

11:32.474 --> 11:35.124
even kept up payments
on life insurance.

11:35.126 --> 11:36.726
Does this mean
that they're gonna

11:36.728 --> 11:38.979
stop searching for Theresa?

11:38.981 --> 11:41.231
Her body, I mean?

11:41.233 --> 11:43.516
The police have concluded
their investigation.

11:43.518 --> 11:45.635
You weren't satisfied?

11:45.637 --> 11:48.021
No, it's-- It's just...

11:48.023 --> 11:49.939
We buried an empty coffin.

11:49.941 --> 11:56.196
They-- They said that the current
would have taken her body,

11:56.198 --> 12:01.835
and I was hoping that maybe
it would bring her home.

12:01.837 --> 12:03.152
[Sighs] I'm sorry.

12:03.154 --> 12:05.622
This is just drudging up
some really difficult memories.

12:05.624 --> 12:09.809
Not at all.
I can only imagine.

12:09.811 --> 12:12.178
Derek never
came out of the funk.

12:12.180 --> 12:13.813
[Sniffs]

12:13.815 --> 12:16.433
Sometimes you just lose people.

12:16.435 --> 12:18.000
You don't have
any contact information

12:18.002 --> 12:19.386
for your ex-husband, do you?

12:19.388 --> 12:21.855
No, we've barely spoken
since we split.

12:21.857 --> 12:23.523
I have a-- An old
cell phone number.

12:23.525 --> 12:26.443
Good luck tracking him down.

12:26.445 --> 12:29.112
You might want to mention
that there's money involved.

12:29.114 --> 12:30.113
I have to ask this.

12:30.115 --> 12:31.614
Did you and Derek
have any children?

12:31.616 --> 12:33.683
No kids.

12:33.685 --> 12:37.520
Now I'm not even an aunt.

12:37.522 --> 12:40.189
Smart as a whip, Theresa.

12:40.191 --> 12:43.543
I loved her like
she was my own daughter.

12:43.545 --> 12:48.231
Unfortunately,
you can't pick your parents.

12:48.233 --> 12:50.550
Unbelievable.

12:50.552 --> 12:53.386
I've got eight case files
connected to this guy's prints,

12:53.388 --> 12:55.638
and half of them
have been redacted.

12:55.640 --> 12:59.175
Here we go.
Missing persons '07.

12:59.177 --> 13:00.560
Your trigger happy hobo,
Carter.

13:00.562 --> 13:02.378
Only now he's a killer
in a suit.

13:02.380 --> 13:04.347
Well, maybe he's
a recovering diplomat.

13:04.349 --> 13:06.099
They pulled the whole file.

13:06.101 --> 13:08.902
Feds. This one's above
your pay grade, Carter.

13:11.572 --> 13:14.107
Aunt's fine.
Uncle's MIA.

13:14.109 --> 13:15.775
MIA?

13:15.777 --> 13:17.577
You got no contact info?

13:17.579 --> 13:19.913
No answer on the cell phone.
No forwarding address.

13:19.915 --> 13:21.197
Where are you?

13:21.199 --> 13:23.316
I've been to every
skate-rat park in the city.

13:23.318 --> 13:25.368
Nothing but attitude on wheels.

13:25.370 --> 13:29.622
No sign of Theresa?

13:29.624 --> 13:34.577
No, but I think
I just found our guy.

13:40.601 --> 13:42.118
What the--?

13:42.120 --> 13:43.686
What's your problem, fool?

13:43.688 --> 13:46.356
$200 fine to skate in the park.

13:46.358 --> 13:49.859
Want to know the last time
you seen this girl, Deacon.

13:49.861 --> 13:51.561
What is this?
Some kind of sick joke?

13:51.563 --> 13:53.262
News flash, chief.

13:53.264 --> 13:55.264
Old man went postal
on her whole family.

13:55.266 --> 13:56.483
She's dead.

13:56.485 --> 13:57.400
Or maybe not.

13:57.402 --> 13:58.701
Maybe you seen her around,
chief.

13:58.703 --> 14:01.604
That girl's gone.
Give me back my phone.

14:11.665 --> 14:13.967
Is he riding you?
What's up with that, man?

14:13.969 --> 14:16.836
[Phone beeps]

14:29.767 --> 14:32.652
[Suspenseful music]

14:32.654 --> 14:38.908
♪ ♪

14:38.910 --> 14:41.411
Theresa.

14:43.380 --> 14:44.948
Theresa.

14:44.950 --> 14:47.750
Wait.

14:52.506 --> 14:54.791
[Tires screech]
Watch it, idiot!

15:25.003 --> 15:26.170
Hi, Harold.

15:26.172 --> 15:28.256
Hello.

15:34.379 --> 15:36.514
Morning, Harold.

15:36.516 --> 15:40.718
Listen, um, that database
you're coding,

15:40.720 --> 15:44.388
we're gonna need it
a little faster, okay?

15:44.390 --> 15:45.907
You-- You got to keep up.

15:45.909 --> 15:49.360
Okay. I'll see
what I can do, Dave.

15:55.751 --> 15:59.036
Not exactly what I expected.

15:59.038 --> 16:02.006
Software engineer of the month.

16:02.008 --> 16:03.407
That's very impressive.

16:03.409 --> 16:06.911
But it doesn't quite explain
the private security,

16:06.913 --> 16:08.679
the unlimited funds.

16:08.681 --> 16:13.100
No.
No, it wouldn't.

16:13.102 --> 16:16.086
I did some digging down in HR.

16:16.088 --> 16:19.223
Seems you've worked here
for 17 years.

16:19.225 --> 16:23.194
Only been promoted twice.

16:23.196 --> 16:27.097
So how many of these people
know you own the entire company?

16:27.099 --> 16:28.533
None of them.

16:28.535 --> 16:32.370
The best place to hide,
Mr. Reese, as you well know,

16:32.372 --> 16:34.489
is in plain sight.

16:34.491 --> 16:36.407
And if I speak too loudly,

16:36.409 --> 16:37.992
say the wrong thing?

16:37.994 --> 16:40.995
The entire department
could be overhauled.

16:40.997 --> 16:45.616
Some would be reassigned,
promoted.

16:45.618 --> 16:49.303
Some would be fired.

16:49.305 --> 16:51.889
I'll make it quick, then.

16:51.891 --> 16:54.392
The good news,
the girl is alive.

16:54.394 --> 16:56.677
And, uh, kicking.

16:56.679 --> 16:59.129
Seems she has
some trust issues.

16:59.131 --> 17:02.733
I, uh, I lost her.

17:02.735 --> 17:05.603
But I did figure out how she's
been providing for herself.

17:05.605 --> 17:08.638
She left this
at an atm machine.

17:08.641 --> 17:09.740
It's a skimmer.

17:09.742 --> 17:14.478
It captures
account numbers and pins.

17:14.480 --> 17:16.196
If she tries
to sell these online,

17:16.199 --> 17:18.082
I might be able
to track her down.

17:18.084 --> 17:19.983
In the meantime,
we need to figure out

17:19.986 --> 17:21.919
who killed her family and why.

17:21.921 --> 17:24.454
Her uncle's hiding from
a dozen different creditors,

17:24.457 --> 17:26.339
but I'll find him.

17:26.342 --> 17:28.993
And I want to look
at Grant Whitaker's finances

17:28.995 --> 17:30.628
much more carefully.

17:30.630 --> 17:31.829
Good.

17:31.831 --> 17:33.714
'Cause this was a hit for hire,

17:33.716 --> 17:35.683
and I'm gonna
look into the shooter.

17:35.685 --> 17:36.884
How?

17:36.886 --> 17:39.353
Find out where I can hire one.

17:44.359 --> 17:48.112
So who's your friend, Harold?

17:53.435 --> 17:55.853
Guy behind the bar's a fixer.

17:55.855 --> 17:59.890
Takes a piece of most
contract killings in the city.

17:59.892 --> 18:01.709
If someone did
wipe out the family,

18:01.711 --> 18:03.661
he might know who did it.

18:03.663 --> 18:05.212
Hey, he don't talk to people

18:05.214 --> 18:06.581
who just walk into the joint.

18:06.583 --> 18:08.799
Lionel, you worried about me?

18:08.801 --> 18:11.702
I'm touched.

18:29.938 --> 18:32.974
Don't let me see you
around here again.

18:42.834 --> 18:45.753
[Suspenseful music]

18:45.755 --> 18:50.591
♪ ♪

18:50.593 --> 18:52.409
[Glass breaking]

18:52.411 --> 18:55.296
[Man yells indistinct,
gun fires]

18:55.298 --> 18:59.133
[Man yells, glass breaks]

18:59.135 --> 19:00.918
[Gun fires]

19:00.920 --> 19:03.270
[Man coughs]

19:10.979 --> 19:13.230
Got a name.

19:13.232 --> 19:15.282
Let's go.

19:15.284 --> 19:17.201
Fusco's CI.
Pointed me towards

19:17.203 --> 19:18.853
a contract killer
named Solnick.

19:18.855 --> 19:22.289
Problem is Solnick got himself
locked up for a separate job,

19:22.291 --> 19:23.491
so I've arranged a visit.

19:23.493 --> 19:26.276
[Door buzzes]

19:29.798 --> 19:33.134
[Guard removes handcuffs]

19:40.142 --> 19:41.509
Who are you?

19:41.511 --> 19:42.793
Did my lawyer quit again?

19:42.795 --> 19:44.128
No.

19:44.130 --> 19:47.181
I'd like to talk to you
about that family you murdered,

19:47.183 --> 19:50.067
then dumped in the Bowery Bay.

19:50.069 --> 19:52.603
What, you don't want
to talk about that one?

19:52.605 --> 19:55.773
How about some of
the other people you killed?

19:55.775 --> 19:57.942
Like that brother
of that gang leader

19:57.944 --> 19:59.443
that lives on your cell block.

19:59.445 --> 20:02.997
I'm sure he'd love to know
his brother's last words.

20:02.999 --> 20:05.416
Hmm?

20:08.870 --> 20:09.987
I get it.

20:09.989 --> 20:11.839
You're like me.

20:11.841 --> 20:13.323
A killer.

20:13.325 --> 20:16.594
A genuine bad guy.

20:16.596 --> 20:18.546
Then I don't have
to explain to you

20:18.548 --> 20:20.965
what happened
to those people on that boat.

20:20.967 --> 20:22.683
You already know.

20:22.685 --> 20:24.268
But what I don't know

20:24.270 --> 20:27.104
is why you let the girl live.

20:27.106 --> 20:28.689
I wouldn't
have killed the girl.

20:28.691 --> 20:31.842
Not even if
they paid me my quote.

20:31.844 --> 20:33.644
I told her anyone
ever knew she was alive,

20:33.646 --> 20:36.063
I'd finish the job.

20:36.065 --> 20:38.282
I don't kill kids.

20:38.284 --> 20:41.235
Had some punk
on my cell block last week

20:41.237 --> 20:42.686
say he heard I did.

20:42.688 --> 20:44.155
I told him the same thing.

20:44.157 --> 20:46.690
Who hired you to do it?

20:46.692 --> 20:49.043
Some guy I met one time.

20:49.045 --> 20:54.465
No names. Cash.

20:54.467 --> 20:57.084
Who hired you?

20:59.104 --> 21:01.505
Guys who kill kids
aren't popular in jail.

21:01.507 --> 21:03.140
Solnick's been
defending his honor.

21:03.142 --> 21:04.258
The people that hired him

21:04.260 --> 21:06.177
may have found out
he didn't kill Theresa.

21:06.179 --> 21:09.396
Maybe they hired somebody new
to finish the job.

21:09.398 --> 21:11.165
Why are they so worried
about a teenager?

21:11.167 --> 21:12.099
I don't know.

21:12.101 --> 21:14.502
But we need
to figure it out fast.

21:14.504 --> 21:17.271
Oh, I think I may have a lead.

21:17.273 --> 21:18.823
Whitaker was sole investor

21:18.825 --> 21:21.492
in all his real estate deals
except one.

21:21.494 --> 21:23.077
He bought a couple
of parcels of landstor

21:23.079 --> 21:26.330
with the real estate
holding company Landale.

21:26.332 --> 21:28.565
Landale.
Send me the address.

21:28.567 --> 21:31.418
I'm on my way.

21:43.298 --> 21:45.766
Landale financial,
second floor.

21:45.768 --> 21:47.818
30 million or so in holdings.

21:47.820 --> 21:50.855
Principal is a guy
named Calhoun.

21:50.857 --> 21:52.923
Well, Calhoun's got
a lot of security

21:52.925 --> 21:55.226
for a real estate developer.

21:55.228 --> 21:59.146
Wait a second.
Who's this?

22:01.599 --> 22:05.653
I think I just found
Theresa's uncle Derek.

22:05.655 --> 22:08.739
Why would he turn up here?

22:08.741 --> 22:10.624
That's gonna have to wait.

22:10.626 --> 22:13.627
Theresa just tried to sell
those account numbers online.

22:13.629 --> 22:17.047
I'm tracing the IP address
where she logged on.

22:17.049 --> 22:19.133
It's at 89th and West End.

22:19.135 --> 22:21.352
Get moving.

22:21.354 --> 22:22.953
Is it a wireless network?

22:22.955 --> 22:24.421
It is.

22:24.423 --> 22:27.675
Maybe she's in one
of the surrounding buildings.

22:38.803 --> 22:40.688
Hey.

22:40.690 --> 22:43.490
You got me pretty good
back there.

22:43.492 --> 22:47.361
Not-- Not looking
for a rematch.

22:47.363 --> 22:51.582
I know what happened
to you and your family.

22:51.584 --> 22:52.833
I'm here to help you.

22:52.835 --> 22:54.285
Just leave me alone.

22:54.287 --> 22:56.337
The man that killed
your family's in jail.

22:56.339 --> 22:58.923
No one's gonna hurt you again.

22:58.925 --> 23:01.658
'Cause I won't let them.

23:01.660 --> 23:04.494
You really shouldn't
lie to kids.

23:05.380 --> 23:08.048
[Grunts]

23:14.439 --> 23:16.724
Aah!
Ugh!

24:06.724 --> 24:09.777
[Groans]

24:11.029 --> 24:15.732
Theresa.
Are you gonna trust me now?

24:15.734 --> 24:17.067
I don't know you.

24:17.069 --> 24:19.920
You're gonna need
to trust someone.

24:30.278 --> 24:31.479
Don't worry.

24:31.481 --> 24:33.864
You're safe here.

24:38.286 --> 24:40.204
Ordered you room service.

24:40.206 --> 24:43.324
It's a $50 cheeseburger.

24:46.545 --> 24:48.445
Theresa.

24:50.048 --> 24:52.282
The man who came after you
at the laundry mat,

24:52.284 --> 24:54.552
you ever see him before?

24:54.554 --> 24:57.788
Do you have any idea
who targeted your family?

24:57.790 --> 24:59.006
No.

24:59.008 --> 25:01.559
Did it have anything
to do with your uncle Derek?

25:01.561 --> 25:02.927
Is that why
you didn't come to him?

25:02.929 --> 25:04.294
I don't trust him.

25:04.296 --> 25:06.013
Why?

25:06.015 --> 25:08.649
What my dad said,

25:08.651 --> 25:11.969
before that man
put a bullet in his head,

25:11.971 --> 25:15.138
he said it was Derek's fault.

25:17.008 --> 25:19.660
[Knock at door]

25:30.288 --> 25:31.288
Hello.

25:31.290 --> 25:32.823
Theresa, this is Harold,

25:32.825 --> 25:34.708
and he's gonna stay with you.

25:34.710 --> 25:35.826
Nice room.

25:35.828 --> 25:37.761
Took the liberty
of booking all four.

25:37.763 --> 25:39.263
Your card.

25:39.265 --> 25:41.182
Guess I can use the miles.

25:41.184 --> 25:43.500
Theresa can't be left alone.

25:43.502 --> 25:47.054
Here.
I better take this.

25:47.056 --> 25:51.225
And, uh, this.

25:52.110 --> 25:54.228
I need you
to stay here with Harold.

25:54.230 --> 25:56.230
He'll take care of you.

25:56.232 --> 25:58.065
Where are you going?

25:58.067 --> 26:04.121
I'm gonna pay a man a visit.

26:04.123 --> 26:06.073
I have the uncle's
cell phone account.

26:06.075 --> 26:07.541
The GPS signal is active,

26:07.543 --> 26:08.659
but he's not answering.

26:08.661 --> 26:10.794
Landale's involved.

26:10.796 --> 26:15.966
I'm just not sure why
they're still coming after her.

26:15.968 --> 26:18.252
Don't dawdle.

26:25.760 --> 26:28.562
[Cell phone rings]

26:31.650 --> 26:34.384
What the hell?

26:34.386 --> 26:38.105
[Keys jangle]

26:38.107 --> 26:39.690
What's the matter, Derek?

26:39.692 --> 26:42.576
You don't want to talk
to your dead brother?

26:44.829 --> 26:46.030
Get in the truck.

26:46.032 --> 26:48.899
I'll drive.

26:48.901 --> 26:51.835
Yeah, Derek, we need to talk.

26:51.837 --> 26:53.337
I left you a couple messages

26:53.339 --> 26:56.790
about the insurance guy
who came by, asking questions.

26:56.792 --> 26:58.092
He wants to talk to you.

26:58.094 --> 27:02.630
Something about Grant's assets
coming out of probate.

27:02.632 --> 27:04.915
I gave him your cell.

27:04.917 --> 27:08.302
Anyway, call me back please.

27:08.304 --> 27:11.272
Sometime this year?

27:18.363 --> 27:21.198
Remember this place, Derek?

27:21.200 --> 27:23.233
Where they dumped
your brother's whole family

27:23.235 --> 27:25.069
in the water like chum.

27:25.071 --> 27:26.954
What are you talking about?

27:26.956 --> 27:28.622
I'm talking business, Derek.

27:28.624 --> 27:31.208
Landale Financial,
where you were yesterday.

27:31.210 --> 27:32.126
Who the hell are you?

27:32.128 --> 27:33.961
That deal your
brother Grant made,

27:33.963 --> 27:36.880
greenpoint, bunch of land
out in Brooklyn

27:36.882 --> 27:38.832
ruined by an oil spill.

27:38.834 --> 27:40.868
And now you're cutting a deal
with him, aren't you?

27:40.870 --> 27:42.619
I tried to help Grant.

27:42.621 --> 27:44.088
You helped him, all right.

27:44.090 --> 27:47.224
Right into an early grave.
With no will.

27:47.226 --> 27:49.510
Which means that land
goes into probate,

27:49.512 --> 27:51.461
and then to you, Derek.

27:51.463 --> 27:56.183
Let me ask you this.

27:56.185 --> 27:58.569
Did you hire
the hit man yourself,

27:58.571 --> 28:00.187
or did you let Landale do it?

28:00.189 --> 28:02.239
I never meant
for anyone to get hurt.

28:02.241 --> 28:05.743
Grant, he swore that greenpoint
was gonna be the big one.

28:05.745 --> 28:07.911
He just didn't have enough
to cover all the parcels,

28:07.913 --> 28:09.813
so I told him
I know these guys.

28:09.815 --> 28:12.282
Calhoun. Landale.

28:12.284 --> 28:13.667
It all looked legit.

28:13.669 --> 28:15.419
It was a front for dirty money.

28:15.421 --> 28:17.671
And you set your brother
up with them.

28:17.673 --> 28:20.724
Grant swore that
it was gonna be a ten-bagger

28:20.726 --> 28:22.993
as soon as the government
cleaned up the site.

28:22.995 --> 28:24.712
But, like everything
with the government,

28:24.714 --> 28:25.713
it took too damn long.

28:25.715 --> 28:27.998
Landale wanted
their money immediately.

28:28.000 --> 28:30.617
So they took him out along
with everyone in his family

28:30.619 --> 28:32.803
just to get their money
back out.

28:32.805 --> 28:35.055
They made me
the administer of probate.

28:35.057 --> 28:38.809
That's the only reason
why they didn't kill me.

28:38.811 --> 28:42.563
I'm supposed to sign it
over to 'em next week.

28:44.348 --> 28:47.684
You know, the kicker is
that Grant was right.

28:47.686 --> 28:49.987
Government came through.
They cleaned up the site.

28:49.989 --> 28:53.857
Now it's worth 20, 30 times
what they put into it.

28:53.859 --> 28:56.960
So that's why they're still
coming after her.

28:56.962 --> 29:00.080
Theresa is the legal heir
to that property.

29:00.082 --> 29:01.698
Theres-- What are you
talking about?

29:01.700 --> 29:02.699
She's dead.

29:02.701 --> 29:04.051
She's alive.

29:04.053 --> 29:05.535
No thanks to you.

29:05.537 --> 29:09.723
If you'd come forward,
cleared your brother's name,

29:09.725 --> 29:12.092
she might not have spent
the last two years hiding.

29:12.094 --> 29:16.379
From you.

29:16.381 --> 29:18.766
You know, I went to see
your aunt Elizabeth.

29:18.768 --> 29:21.018
She seems like a lovely person.

29:21.020 --> 29:22.686
You tell her about me?

29:22.688 --> 29:25.489
No. Of course not.

29:25.491 --> 29:29.993
But she did mention
how much she missed you.

29:29.995 --> 29:34.081
She even showed me
an old photo.

29:34.083 --> 29:37.901
You know, there's no changing
what happened to your family,

29:37.903 --> 29:40.788
but you do have someone
out there that loves you.

29:40.790 --> 29:43.474
Yeah?
What do you know?

29:43.476 --> 29:47.511
I know what it's like
to lose someone.

29:47.513 --> 29:51.748
And to feel the need
to disappear.

29:51.750 --> 29:56.069
But, trust me, you don't want
to leave people behind.

30:16.624 --> 30:20.944
When were you going to tell me?

30:20.946 --> 30:24.131
I wasn't gonna tell you,
I guess.

30:24.133 --> 30:27.417
I'd rather
I didn't know myself.

30:27.419 --> 30:29.803
All these people.

30:29.805 --> 30:31.989
And this damn machine knew.

30:31.991 --> 30:33.557
You knew...

30:33.559 --> 30:35.859
That someone wanted
to harm them,

30:35.861 --> 30:40.597
kill them...

30:40.599 --> 30:42.933
And you did nothing?

30:42.935 --> 30:48.739
You knew what
we were building here.

30:48.741 --> 30:52.860
This thing looks for plotters,
for schemers.

30:52.862 --> 30:54.611
It looks for malicious intent.

30:54.613 --> 30:57.281
We built it to stop terrorists
before they could act.

30:57.283 --> 30:59.616
But a machine doesn't
understand the difference

30:59.618 --> 31:02.819
between those crimes that are
relevant to national security

31:02.821 --> 31:06.323
and the ones
that are irrelevant.

31:07.992 --> 31:13.013
Irrelevant?

31:13.015 --> 31:15.966
So you taught it
the difference?

31:15.968 --> 31:17.885
You want to play God?
Is that the deal?

31:17.887 --> 31:20.771
No, I don't.
That's the whole point.

31:20.773 --> 31:22.472
There are exactly
eight people in the world

31:22.474 --> 31:24.641
that know
that this thing exists.

31:24.643 --> 31:26.143
If anyone else ever found out,

31:26.145 --> 31:30.513
there'd be such an outcry...
They'd turn it off.

31:30.515 --> 31:33.734
The intelligence
the machine produces

31:33.736 --> 31:39.239
has already foiled a half dozen
major terrorist plots.

31:39.241 --> 31:41.524
How are we supposed
to live with this,

31:41.526 --> 31:44.878
knowing that someone
out there needs help?

31:47.465 --> 31:48.715
Well, we don't have to.

31:48.717 --> 31:51.552
I've coded the machine.

31:51.554 --> 31:53.036
Every night at midnight,

31:53.038 --> 31:56.256
it deletes the irrelevant list.

31:56.258 --> 31:59.893
We didn't build this
to save somebody.

31:59.895 --> 32:03.546
We built it to save everybody.

32:13.908 --> 32:16.243
Where's the girl?

32:19.163 --> 32:22.416
Kid's worth a fortune, Finch.

32:22.418 --> 32:25.285
Land the father bought
panned out fifty fold.

32:25.287 --> 32:26.620
And Landale wants it all.

32:26.622 --> 32:27.788
Killed the whole family.

32:27.790 --> 32:29.706
Expected to clean up
after it cleared probate.

32:29.708 --> 32:31.842
'Til they found out
the girl was still alive.

32:31.844 --> 32:33.410
Do we know who ordered the hit?

32:33.412 --> 32:36.179
Calhoun, the father's
business partner.

32:36.181 --> 32:37.848
I've got eyes on him.

32:37.850 --> 32:40.917
And he's walking.

32:40.919 --> 32:42.919
So's Theresa.
Got to go.

32:45.223 --> 32:47.391
Wait. Theresa.

32:47.393 --> 32:49.226
You know I can't
keep up with you.

32:49.228 --> 32:51.361
Can I ask you
where you're going?

32:51.363 --> 32:52.663
I'm better off alone.

32:52.665 --> 32:54.948
And how's that?

32:54.950 --> 32:56.450
It's safer.

32:56.452 --> 32:58.652
I don't think so.

32:58.654 --> 33:00.320
Please.

33:00.322 --> 33:01.771
Sooner or later,

33:01.773 --> 33:03.940
you're gonna have
to trust someone.

33:07.662 --> 33:10.447
You can't kill me.

33:10.449 --> 33:13.800
They need me.

33:13.802 --> 33:17.004
See...

33:17.006 --> 33:22.976
You have vastly overestimated
your value in this process.

33:24.429 --> 33:28.649
They'll just hire
another couple of lawyers.

33:28.651 --> 33:31.234
So.

33:31.236 --> 33:34.888
I'll ask you one more time.

33:34.890 --> 33:37.407
Where's the girl?

33:42.246 --> 33:44.831
Kiss my ass.

33:51.539 --> 33:53.156
[Gun fires]

33:55.510 --> 33:57.044
Can't tell you how much

33:57.046 --> 33:59.596
we appreciate your patience
and support on this, councilman.

33:59.598 --> 34:01.381
You're sure we're
free and clear on this?

34:01.383 --> 34:04.000
Rezoned for residential.

34:04.002 --> 34:06.136
Hell, you can break ground
as early as next month.

34:06.138 --> 34:07.804
Jimmy Calhoun.

34:07.806 --> 34:08.755
I got to hand it to you.

34:08.757 --> 34:10.440
You really turned
this thing around,

34:10.442 --> 34:12.509
saw what nobody else did
on the property.

34:12.511 --> 34:14.277
This is a real game-changer.

34:14.279 --> 34:15.362
Thank you, sir.

34:15.364 --> 34:17.563
The good people of Brooklyn
deserve it, sir.

34:17.565 --> 34:19.983
Look forward to it, Jim.

34:21.768 --> 34:23.954
[Police radio chatters]

34:26.741 --> 34:28.291
- Hey.
- Hey.

34:28.293 --> 34:29.609
Neighbor called it in.

34:29.610 --> 34:30.911
Thought they heard a dispute.

34:30.913 --> 34:32.161
A dispute.

34:32.164 --> 34:34.081
- Yeah.
- You think?

34:34.083 --> 34:36.166
Yeah, thank goodness
for vigilant neighbors, huh?

34:36.168 --> 34:41.388
Oh, yeah. Found this
stuffed in his mouth.

34:41.389 --> 34:44.507
We got to find out
who this girl is.

34:44.510 --> 34:46.927
[Dials number]

34:51.549 --> 34:54.568
[Telephone rings]

34:54.570 --> 34:56.770
[Cell phone rings]

35:02.243 --> 35:04.394
Hello?

35:04.396 --> 35:07.564
Hello?

35:07.566 --> 35:09.249
Who is this?

35:09.251 --> 35:11.785
Hello?

35:11.787 --> 35:13.620
[Phone beeps]

35:23.848 --> 35:26.183
Thank you for calling
The Fenwick, New York.

35:26.185 --> 35:28.268
How can I assist you?

35:33.975 --> 35:36.426
[Cell phone beeps]

35:52.410 --> 35:55.328
[Rock music]

35:55.330 --> 36:00.283
♪ ♪

36:03.254 --> 36:05.755
Sorry.

36:05.757 --> 36:08.958
You really need to watch
where you're going.

36:13.297 --> 36:14.964
Call off the dogs.

36:14.966 --> 36:18.134
Theresa Whitaker.
Right now.

36:18.136 --> 36:19.769
It's too--
It's too late.

36:19.771 --> 36:22.972
It's done.
It's already done.

36:25.910 --> 36:28.978
He's coming, Finch.
Get off that floor.

36:28.980 --> 36:31.865
We have to go.
Now.

36:46.547 --> 36:48.765
[Elevator bell dings]

37:15.542 --> 37:18.377
I can see him.

37:18.379 --> 37:24.216
He's coming down the hall.

37:24.218 --> 37:25.401
He's going for the fuse box.

37:25.403 --> 37:27.153
He's gonna cut out the lights
in the hallway.

37:27.155 --> 37:29.221
He's gonna see the lights
in our room.

37:29.223 --> 37:32.124
Quick.
Turn 'em all off.

37:57.467 --> 37:59.969
[Thud]

38:05.258 --> 38:06.726
I told you we should have left.

38:06.728 --> 38:09.311
You did.
I'm sorry.

38:18.572 --> 38:21.540
Give me your phone.

38:22.826 --> 38:24.443
What are we doing?
I don't understand.

38:24.445 --> 38:26.712
- Just--just...
- Wait. Hurry up.

38:28.281 --> 38:29.298
- Shh.
- Let's go.

38:29.300 --> 38:32.301
Shh. Shh.
Don't...

38:32.303 --> 38:33.552
This isn't gonna work.

38:33.554 --> 38:35.254
He's coming.
He's right outside the door.

38:35.256 --> 38:37.723
I know.
I know he is.

38:42.429 --> 38:43.462
No, no, no.
Too slow.

38:43.464 --> 38:47.149
Come on.
This way.

38:56.777 --> 39:00.196
We haven't got much time.

39:02.982 --> 39:05.084
He's here.

39:05.086 --> 39:07.369
Fire escape.
You can go down.

39:07.371 --> 39:10.623
Come on.
Go. Go.

39:10.625 --> 39:13.325
You coming?

39:13.327 --> 39:14.326
I can't get through there.

39:14.328 --> 39:16.662
You have to go without me.

39:16.664 --> 39:20.633
I'm staying with you.

39:43.206 --> 39:47.192
[Telephone rings]

39:47.194 --> 39:48.294
Yeah. Carter.

39:48.296 --> 39:50.379
You been asking a lot
of questions about me.

39:50.381 --> 39:52.464
It's time we sat down
face to face.

39:52.466 --> 39:53.632
Who is this?

39:53.634 --> 39:57.086
You know who.
You want to meet me or not?

39:57.088 --> 39:59.538
Go.

40:09.766 --> 40:11.183
Wait for my signal.

40:11.185 --> 40:13.051
Be careful.

40:13.053 --> 40:16.105
This guy's as dangerous
as they get.

40:47.086 --> 40:49.555
Sweetheart?
What are you doing here?

40:49.557 --> 40:50.940
Are you detective Carter?

40:50.942 --> 40:52.391
Yes.

40:52.393 --> 40:55.110
My friend said
I could trust you.

41:18.718 --> 41:21.637
Watch your head,
Mr. Calhoun.

41:21.639 --> 41:23.422
So you can't tell me anything

41:23.424 --> 41:27.459
about how this man looks?

41:27.461 --> 41:29.762
Hotel staff said
they might have seen

41:29.764 --> 41:31.513
two people coming and going,

41:31.515 --> 41:36.435
but it's nothing on
the surveillance cameras.

41:36.437 --> 41:40.773
Was there anyone else
helping you?

41:40.775 --> 41:45.194
It was a pretty
traumatic experience.

41:45.196 --> 41:47.780
I don't remember much at all.

41:50.867 --> 41:53.819
[Downbeat jazz music]

41:53.821 --> 42:01.627
♪ ♪

42:08.301 --> 42:11.186
Theresa.

42:11.188 --> 42:13.555
Oh.

42:30.991 --> 42:33.459
Are you looking for Harold?

42:33.461 --> 42:36.045
Is he taking
another personal day?

42:36.047 --> 42:39.832
I don't think so.
I was hoping you knew.

42:39.834 --> 42:41.417
Maggie said
he'd been transferred,

42:41.419 --> 42:42.918
but Dave said he was laid off.

42:42.920 --> 42:45.587
He didn't even say goodbye.

42:45.589 --> 42:49.591
[Cell phone rings]

42:49.593 --> 42:51.060
And here I was thinking

42:51.062 --> 42:53.479
we were getting
a little closer, Harold.

42:53.481 --> 42:55.514
I told you I'm
a very private person.

42:55.516 --> 42:57.883
Well, you're gonna need
to trust someone at some point.

42:57.885 --> 43:01.854
Trust? That's not something
I come by very easily.

43:01.856 --> 43:03.305
I have my reasons.

43:03.307 --> 43:07.710
Are you ever gonna
tell me those reasons?

43:07.712 --> 43:10.195
Don't call me,
Mr. Reese.

43:10.197 --> 43:13.449
I'll call you.

